06/04/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- Mayor Dora Bakoyianni said Monday (5 April) that those attending the Summer Olympics should not be deterred by the fear of terrorism. "I have personal experience and I believe if you give up and allow terrorists to change your life, then they have won without even having done something," she said. The terrorist group 17 November killed her first husband.
Public Order Minister Giorgos Voulgarakis, meanwhile, met senior Portuguese officials to discuss security for large-scale events. Portugal hosts the European soccer championship in June.
Also Monday, Athens 2004 Olympic Games Organising Committee President Gianna Angelopoulos-Daskalaki updated Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis on preparations, while Finance Minister George Alogoskoufis approved the release of 558.9m euros in project financing to pay for landscaping and infrastructure. (AP, ANA, MPA - 05/04/04)
